&lt;p&gt;C3EL is seeking a Senior IT Systems Engineer to support IT operations in Washington, DC. This role is responsible for the design, implementation, and maintenance of complex IT systems to ensure reliability, performance, and scalability. The selected candidate will provide technical leadership across system architecture, integration, and operational support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain systems, including servers, virtualization, storage, and cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, configure, and manage Windows and Linux operating systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor system performance and troubleshoot hardware, software, and infrastructure issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support system integration and ensure interoperability across platforms and applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement backup, recovery, and disaster recovery solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering teams to ensure systems are secure and aligned with best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate administrative tasks using scripting tools (e.g., PowerShell, Python, Bash).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain system documentation, configurations, and standard operating procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical guidance to junior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
