&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C3EL is seeking a cleared Senior Network Engineer to join our on-site team at Fort Shafter Flats in Honolulu, Hawaii. This position is responsible for the design, installation, configuration, and maintenance of core network infrastructure solutions supporting Department of Defense operations. The Senior Network Engineer will ensure high availability, security, and performance of enterprise routing, switching, and VoIP environments in accordance with DoD and DISA standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, engineer, and maintain enterprise routing and switching environments utilizing EIGRP, OSPF, BGP, and multicast protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and manage VPN and firewall solutions to ensure secure communications across the enterprise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate and maintain VoIP and CENTRIX systems in compliance with mission requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and support core network infrastructure components to ensure reliability and redundancy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct network performance monitoring, optimization, and troubleshooting for complex systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all configurations meet DISA STIG and DoD cybersecurity compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain detailed network documentation, including topology diagrams and configuration baselines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with government stakeholders and engineering teams to plan and execute infrastructure upgrades and modernization initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
