&lt;p&gt;C3EL is seeking a cleared &lt;strong&gt;Senior Systems Administrator &amp;amp; VMware Professional&lt;/strong&gt; to join our on-site team at Fort Shafter Flats in Honolulu, Hawaii. This position is responsible for the configuration, maintenance, and optimization of enterprise server and virtualization environments supporting critical Department of Defense operations. The Senior Administrator will oversee Windows, UNIX, and SQL systems; manage enterprise storage and virtualization infrastructure; and ensure full compliance with DoD cybersecurity and configuration standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure, manage, and maintain Windows, UNIX, and SQL servers in an enterprise environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and optimize VMware virtualization technologies, including ESX, ESXi, and vSphere platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain Security Technical Implementation Guides (STIGs) to ensure systems meet DoD security compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and support enterprise storage solutions (SAN, iSCSI, and related technologies).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and monitor fiber channel networks (Brocade, Cisco, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute backup and disaster recovery solutions for enterprise systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer Linux servers and provide scripting or automation support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee system performance, patching, and updates in accordance with DoD and organizational policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support database administration and maintenance activities for SQL environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain system documentation and configuration baselines to ensure operational integrity and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
