&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer, install, configure, and maintain enterprise servers, including Domain Controllers, File/Print servers, and Proxy systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and enforce DISA Security Technical Implementation Guides (STIGs) across all managed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and maintain Altiris and SCCM solutions for patch management, software deployment, and system imaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deploy automation scripts (PowerShell, VBScript, etc.) to enhance system efficiency and automate Active Directory management tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer enterprise storage solutions (NAS, iSCSI, DAS) and ensure data integrity and system availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support database administration functions for MS SQL and Oracle environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage enterprise DHCP solutions (Lucent, Microsoft DHCP, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide advanced troubleshooting and Tier 3 support for complex enterprise system issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate system documentation and ensure compliance with configuration management standards.&lt;/li&gt;
