&lt;h2 class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;iCIMS_Expandable_Text&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C3EL is seeking a cleared &lt;strong&gt;Senior Telecommunications Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our on-site team at Fort Shafter Flats in Honolulu, Hawaii. This position is responsible for the design, installation, configuration, and maintenance of telecommunication systems supporting Department of Defense operations. The engineer will manage PBX and VoIP infrastructures, oversee circuit provisioning and maintenance, and ensure continuous, secure voice communications across the enterprise environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, configure, and maintain medium to large-scale PBX systems and associated components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and support voicemail systems (Meridian Mail, CallPilot) and signaling servers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and maintain dialing plans, VoIP solutions, and trunk lines including T-1s, PRIs, BRIs, and analog circuits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and support telephony rectifiers and battery backup systems to ensure operational continuity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct daily Moves, Adds, and Changes (MACs) for telecommunications infrastructure and end-user services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and maintain inside plant (ISP) telecommunications infrastructure, including new line installations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Public Address (PA) zones as required by the mission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support integration and migration efforts to VoSIP and other DoD-approved VoIP technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems are maintained in compliance with DoD security and operational standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain accurate system documentation, configurations, and maintenance logs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
